en_727155_0	Chairman of the National Free Teachers Association, SudanthaRatnayake states that the planned trade union action of some Teachers Associations will be futile.
en_727155_1	SudanthaRatnayake said that though speculations are doing rounds teachers will work as usual tomorrow.
en_727155_2	He expects more than 70 percent of teachers will be represent tomorrow as per their surveys.
en_727155_3	Minister AkilaVirajKariyawasam said that the education sector should not be used on behalf of political victimization.
en_727155_4	The Education Minister made this appeal at a media conference organized to raise awareness on the false report that was published in a national newspaper under the headline “All Schools will close on 04th of this month.”He also queried whether schools can be closed in a manner to meet the needs of others.
en_727155_5	In the same newspaper there is an editorial saying that Akila should go to school again.
en_727155_6	He said that this matter was not to be questioned.
